BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Swann" column by Ricardo Boechat: "Brothers"] </F>
  [Text] During a dinner he hosted yesterday for members of 
foreign delegations who will be attending his inauguration, 
South African President Nelson Mandela conferred for a long time 
with Brazilian Foreign Minister Celso Amorim. 
  Among all the foreign dignitaries in attendance, Mandela 
conferred for the longest time with Amorim. 
  Conveying thanks, Mandela said: Brazilian help was decisive 
in our defeat of apartheid. 

